Preheat the #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} lengthways, quartering any larger pieces. Pop
them onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} then season with half the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Rub the potatoes to coat in the oil then arrange them cut-side down on the
baking tray.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until fork tender, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
the tray halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, deseed and finely chop the @chilli{1}.

Trim the @cucumber{2} and quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Run the #peeler{} down its length to make ribbons,
stopping at the core.

In a #bowl{}, toss the cucumber, carrot, @miso paste{2%sachets}, @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and half the chilli (use less if you don't like spice). Set aside, continuing to stir occasionally. Drain any liquid before serving.

> Double sugar for 4 servings.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g}. Season with @salt{to taste}
and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
> due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Add the remaining @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} to the chicken and fry until
fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste} and @teriyaki sauce{1%sachet} to the pan. Toss
the chicken in the sauce to coat well.

Place the @bao buns{6} on a #plate{} (three at a time). Microwave covered for
~{1%minute}. Keep covered until serving.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! To steam the bao instead, place a large pot
> with 2cm of water over high heat. Once boiling, place a colander lined with
> a baking sheet on the pot. Place the bao (three at a time) on the baking
> sheet, cover and steam for 3-4 mins.

Fill the warm bao with teriyaki chicken and some miso marinated veg.

Serve the roast potatoes and remaining veg alongside. Garnish the bao with a
scattering of @peanuts{20%g} and the remaining chopped chilli (use less if you
don't like spice).